#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:2 4a0f927b6d494d5fb7686227e8503aaf
msgid "奉加PB系列"
msgstr "Phyplus PB Series"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:5 74aedbd766894949bb1b011e8bfafca6
msgid "1. 简介"
msgstr "1. Introduction"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:6 5d79f2ac5bcd4029ab1ab945522d9c42
msgid "安信可科技针对物联网设计通用型的蓝牙模组，其功能强大、用途广泛。可以用于智能灯、智能插座、智能空调等其他智能家电。同时符合BLE 5.0及SIG Mesh规范，可直接通过智能手机组建Mesh网络，也可对接天猫精灵等智能音箱，适用于多种智能家居应用场景。"
msgstr "Ai-Thinker Technology has designed a general-purpose Bluetooth module for IoT applications. It is powerful and widely applicable, and can be used in smart lights, smart sockets, smart air conditioners, and other smart home appliances. It also complies with BLE 5.0 and SIG Mesh specifications. A Mesh network can be created directly via a smartphone, and it can also be connected to smart speakers such as Tmall Genie, making it suitable for various smart home application scenarios."

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:8 b4e80052c70d4cc5ada4a2345f00a685
msgid "1.1mm 间距 SMD-20 封装；6 路 PWM 输出；"
msgstr "1.1mm pitch SMD-20 package; 6-channel PWM output;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:9 238102bf440f4395a43a18aad480eec3
msgid "采用BLE 5.0 协议，支Sig Mesh，支持天猫精灵/APP语音控制。"
msgstr "Uses the BLE 5.0 protocol, supports SIG Mesh, and supports Tmall Genie / APP voice control;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:10 4a9012d746d44cedba6cb323fbddf54c
msgid "支持半孔焊盘和天线孔和板载天线。半孔焊盘可把天线引导主板上，天线孔可在模组上直接焊接弹簧天线；"
msgstr "Supports castellated pads, antenna holes, and an onboard antenna. The castellated pads can route the antenna to the mainboard, while the antenna hole allows a spring antenna to be soldered directly onto the module;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:11 32243362765c4441b33676034f77f98e
#, python-format
msgid "亮度（占空比）调整范围 5%-100%，PWM 输出频率 1KHz；"
msgstr "Brightness (duty cycle) adjustment range: 5%-100%, PWM output frequency: 1kHz;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:12 09301a9bfc854210b60d1521377d6382
msgid "支持ESP32-G蓝牙网关通讯，实现远程随时随地控制；"
msgstr "Supports communication with the ESP32-G Bluetooth gateway, enabling remote control anytime and anywhere;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:13 ec89072c235b403e8bba7480671138c5
msgid "支持windows环境SDK二次开发，资料代码全部开源，支持AT指令接入天猫精灵；"
msgstr "Supports secondary development with the SDK in a Windows environment. All documentation and code are open source. Supports AT command access to Tmall Genie;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:14 8bd24780430a4244ba654fd7df1c04b4
msgid "支持Android/IOS APP和微信小程序控制；"
msgstr "Supports Android/iOS apps and WeChat Mini Program control;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:16 8542e589d1b04a6b9a4b6fa472ee10bf
msgid "更多资料请转跳： `安信可官方docs <https://docs.ai-thinker.com/blue_tooth_pb>`__"
msgstr "For more information, please visit: `Ai-Thinker official docs <https://docs.ai-thinker.com/blue_tooth_pb>`__"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:19 b6c772835f0d4f8790493c5628801328
msgid "2. 开发环境搭建"
msgstr "2. Setting Up the Development Environment"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:22 792a64076ac149d788a5c7b4e5c211a0
msgid "2.1 BLE基础知识"
msgstr "2.1 BLE Basics"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:23 04de46a6ca5d49e7932f02c92cc475ea
msgid "Ble 协议栈中的 GAP 层负责处理设备访问模式，包括设备发现、建立连接、终止连接、初始化安全管理和设备配置，所以在 ble 协议栈中有不少函数均是以 GAP 为前缀，这些函数会负责以上的内容。 GAP 层总是作为下面四个钟角色之一："
msgstr "The GAP layer in the BLE protocol stack is responsible for handling device access modes, including device discovery, connection establishment, connection termination, security management initialization, and device configuration. Therefore, many functions in the BLE protocol stack are prefixed with GAP, and these functions are responsible for the tasks mentioned above. The GAP layer always operates as one of the following four roles:"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:26 1ae1bd11bd7e4437ba1e4ea2139361ac
msgid "Broadcaster 广播者——不可以连接的一直在广播的设备；"
msgstr "Broadcaster — A device that continuously broadcasts and cannot be connected;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:27 2cf0aac700f04eb1a8af099667402d1f
msgid "Observer 观测者——可扫描广播设备，但不能发起建立连接的设备；"
msgstr "Observer — A device that can scan broadcasting devices but cannot initiate a connection;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:28 87504959d8f84b8183be1960d3f0a13f
msgid "Peripheral 从机 ——可被连接的广播设备，可以在单个链路层连接中作从机。"
msgstr "Peripheral — A connectable broadcasting device that can act as a slave in a single link-layer connection;"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:29 e0c938b87d1e416b876b14998b5d437a
msgid "Central 主机 ——可以扫描广播设备并发起连接，在单个链路层或多链路层中"
msgstr "Central — A device that can scan broadcasting devices and initiate connections, in a single link-layer or multi-link-layer connection"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:30 2aae4552fb414611955f74f97e47519c
msgid "作为主机。"
msgstr "acts as a master."

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:31 9df1dc4bbce74614a84f4dc485480798
msgid "在典型的蓝牙低功耗系统中，从机设备广播特定的数据，以便让主机知道他是一个可以连接的设备，广播内容包括设备地址以及一些额外的数据，如设备名、服务等。主机收到广播数据后，会向从机发送扫描请求 ScanRequest，然后从机将特定的数据回应给主机，称为扫描回应 ScanResponse。主机收到扫描回应后，便知道这是一个可以建立连接的外部设备，这就是设备发现的全过程。此时，主机可以向从机发起建立连接的请求，连接请求包括下面一些参数。"
msgstr "In a typical Bluetooth Low Energy system, a peripheral device broadcasts specific data so that the central device knows it is a connectable device. The broadcast content includes the device address and some additional data, such as the device name and services. After receiving the broadcast data, the central device sends a ScanRequest to the peripheral device. The peripheral device then responds with specific data, called a ScanResponse. After receiving the scan response, the central device knows that this is an external device that can establish a connection. This is the complete device discovery process. At this point, the central device can initiate a connection request to the peripheral device. The connection request includes the following parameters:"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:32 855b637cde784a6db5ace0e4d0e6481e
msgid "连接间隔——在两个 BLE 设备的连接中使用调频机制，两个设备使用特定的信道收发数据，然后过一段时间后再使用新的信道。（链路层处理信道切换），两设备在信道切换后收发数据称之为连接事件，即使没有应用数据的收发，两个设备任然会通过交换链路层数据来维持连接，连接间隔就是两个连接事件之间的时间间隔，连接间隔以1.25ms 为单位，连接间隔的值为 6（7.5ms）~3200（4s）。"
msgstr "Connection interval — In a connection between two BLE devices, a frequency-hopping mechanism is used. The two devices transmit and receive data on a specific channel, then switch to a new channel after a period of time. (Channel switching is handled by the link layer.) The data transmission and reception after the channel switch is called a connection event. Even when no application data is transmitted or received, the two devices still exchange link-layer data to maintain the connection. The connection interval is the time interval between two connection events. It is measured in units of 1.25ms, with a value range of 6 (7.5ms) to 3200 (4s)."

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:33 aeb5fa3aee5b4e5cb21f1f3427971d33
msgid "从机延时——这个参数的设置可以使从机跳过若干连接事件，这给了从机更多的灵活度，如果它没有数据发送时，可以选择跳过连接时间继续休眠，以节省功耗。"
msgstr "Slave latency — This parameter allows the slave device to skip several connection events, giving the slave more flexibility. If it has no data to send, it can skip the connection event and continue sleeping to reduce power consumption."

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:34 24129bf8e9b64a76bfe9bb079be384eb
msgid "管理超时——这是两个成功连接事件之间的最大允许的间隔，如果超过了这个时间"
msgstr "Supervision timeout — This is the maximum allowed interval between two successful connection events. If this time is exceeded"

#: ../../source/docs/development-environment/BT/pb.rst:35 d569608e7b424b35958fbdcf93627709
msgid "（这个值的单位是 10ms）而没有成功的连接事件，设备被认为丢失连接，返回到未 连接状态，管理超时的范围是 100（100ms）~3200（32s）另外，超时值必须大于有效的连接间隔[有效的连接间隔=连接间隔*（1+从机延时）]。 - 安全管理——只有已认证的连接中，特定的数据数据才能被读写，一旦连接建立，两个设备进行配对，当配对完成后，形成加密连接的密钥，在典型的应用中，外设请求集中器提供密钥来完成配对工作。密钥是一个固定的值，如 000000，也可以随机生成一个数据提供给使用者，当主机设备发送正确的密钥后，两设备交换安全密钥并加密认证链接。在许多情况下，同一对外设和主机会不时的连接和断开，ble 的安全机制中有一项特性，允许两个设备之间建立长久的安全密钥信息，这种特性称为绑定，他允许两设备连接时快速的完成加密认证，而不需要每次连接时执行配对的完整过程。"
msgstr "(the unit of this value is 10ms) and no successful connection event occurs, the device is considered to have lost the connection and returns to the disconnected state. The supervision timeout range is 100 (100ms) to 3200 (32s). In addition, the timeout value must be greater than the effective connection interval [effective connection interval = connection interval × (1 + slave latency)]. - Security management — Only in authenticated connections can specific data be read and written. Once a connection is established, the two devices perform pairing. After pairing is completed, a key for the encrypted connection is generated. In typical applications, the peripheral requests the central device to provide a key to complete the pairing process. The key may be a fixed value, such as 000000, or a randomly generated number provided to the user. When the central device sends the correct key, the two devices exchange security keys and encrypt the authenticated link. In many cases, the same pair of peripheral and central devices may connect and disconnect from time to time. The BLE security mechanism includes a feature that allows two devices to establish long-term security key information. This feature is called bonding. It allows the two devices to quickly complete encryption and authentication when reconnecting, without having to perform the full pairing process every time."

